<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Does anyone else agree that /anon is ridiculous?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Leexa Kudrow">Leexa Kudrow</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 6:13 p.m. 10/6/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Does anyone else agree that /anon is ridiculous?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>When you go into any zone, there are only one or two people without Anonymous turned on. I've asked about a dozen people why they do this, and most haven't given me anything resembling a good answer. One Dark Elf said it was to be mysterious (which was for a RP reason), but most said it was just to avoid getting PKed. So, I ask you, if someone is going to take the time to do a /who and hunt down people near their level, don't they have a good reason to do so? Having Anon turned off means people can find you. Why is that good? It's good because people can ask you to be part of their group instead of /shouting it all over the zone that they need volunteers. It's good because if someone is trying to hunt you down across zones, their only valid reason would be a (probably RP related) vendetta, which only lends to the atmosphere of the game. So can someone give me one good reason why we should all turn on Anonymous inside Rallos Zek?

</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
